
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor yellow

' Entities
class ResearchGroup {
    +String id
    +String name
    +List<Researcher> researchers
    +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
}

class Researcher {
    +String id
    +String name
    +String researchGroup
    +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
}

class Project {
    +String id
    +String name
    +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
}

class WorkPackage {
    +String id
    +String name
    +ResearchGroup leaderGroup
    +List<Researcher> teamMembers
    +Project project
}

' Relationships
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : belongsTo
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : leads
Researcher "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : assignedTo
Project "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : contains

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`ResearchGroup`** is responsible for leading one or more **`WorkPackage`**s.
- **`Researcher`** can be part of exactly one **`ResearchGroup`**, but can be assigned to any **`WorkPackage`**, regardless of its leader group.
- A **`WorkPackage`** has a **leader group** and a list of **team members** (researchers).
- **`Project`** contains multiple **`WorkPackage`**s.

### Notes:
- The diagram reflects the traceability requirement by tracking which researchers are assigned to which WPs, even if they belong to different groups.
- When a researcher changes groups or a WP leadership changes, the assignments are updated accordingly, ensuring accurate service delivery records.

